<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="barrier-n">barrier <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'bæriə(r)/    美 /'bæriər/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-c">1.★ <strong>[C] 屏障；障碍 (物)；关卡：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The mountains form a natural <strong>barrier between</strong> the two countries.
群山构成了两国之间天然的屏障。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The skin acts as a <strong>barrier against</strong> disease, poisons and the sun’s harmful rays. 
皮肤是抵御疾病、毒物和有害太阳射线的屏障。</p><footer>人教⑤ – 5</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a ticket barrier 
检票口</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a <strong>barrier to</strong> success 
成功的障碍</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He overcame the <strong>language barrier</strong>. 
他克服了语言障碍。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Carbon dioxide, which makes a <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ between us and the sun, prevents heat from getting out of the atmosphere easily, so the earth is becoming warmer.  （2013 湖北）<br />
A.difference<br />
B.comparison<br />
C.connection<br />
D.barrier  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. D  </p></div>